author: Shelli Weinstein, TV GUIDE
title: Hillary Clinton Will Visit Stephen Colbert's Late Show
text:
Stephen Colbert has booked his latest presidential guest.
Colbert announced on Twitter Friday that Hillary Clinton will be visiting for theOct. 27 episode of The Late Show and joked that he "can't wait to find out what project she's promoting."
Excited to welcome @HillaryClinton to #LSSC on October 27! Can't wait to find out what project she's promoting.
- Stephen Colbert (@StephenAtHome) October 16, 2015 Colbert has hosted a fair share of political guests in the short month since starting his new hosting gig. Jeb Bush appeared on his debut episode, and Bernie Sanders , Ted Cruz and Donald Trump have also stopped by.
The Late Show with Stephen Colbert airs weeknights at 11:35/10:35c on CBS.
